    "R. Alan Culpepper": "42). Regardless, with the failure\nand flight of the disciples (14:50), the\nwomen now stand in as their surrogates\nin the Gospel narrative, witnessing Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]`\u2019\ndeath and burial and caring for his body\n(cf. the role of John `[char_John_Ref]`\u2019s disciples in 6:29).\nRecapping the Gospel story, Mark adds\n567\n[v_Mrk_15_1] [v_Mrk_15_2] [v_Mrk_15_3] [v_Mrk_15_4] [v_Mrk_15_5] [v_Mrk_15_6] [v_Mrk_15_7] [v_Mrk_15_8] [v_Mrk_15_9] [v_Mrk_15_10] [v_Mrk_15_11] [v_Mrk_15_12] [v_Mrk_15_13] [v_Mrk_15_14] [v_Mrk_15_15] [v_Mrk_15_16] [v_Mrk_15_17] [v_Mrk_15_18] [v_Mrk_15_19] [v_Mrk_15_20] [v_Mrk_15_21] [v_Mrk_15_22] [v_Mrk_15_23] [v_Mrk_15_24] [v_Mrk_15_25] [v_Mrk_15_26] [v_Mrk_15_27] [v_Mrk_15_28] [v_Mrk_15_29] [v_Mrk_15_30] [v_Mrk_15_31] [v_Mrk_15_32] [v_Mrk_15_33] [v_Mrk_15_34] [v_Mrk_15_35] [v_Mrk_15_36] [v_Mrk_15_37] [v_Mrk_15_38] [v_Mrk_15_39] [v_Mrk_15_40] [v_Mrk_15_41] [v_Mrk_15_42] [v_Mrk_15_43] [v_Mrk_15_44] [v_Mrk_15_45] [v_Mrk_15_46] [v_Mrk_15_47] Mark 15:1-47\nThe Lists of Women at the Cross\n[v_Mrk_15_40] Mark 15:40\nMary Magdalene\nMary `[char_Mary_Ref]` the mother of James\nthe Younger and of Joses\nSalome\n[v_Mat_27_56] Matt 27:56\nMary Magdalene\nMary `[char_Mary_Ref]` the mother of James\nand of Joseph `[char_Joseph_Ref]`\nThe mother of the sons of\nZebedee\n[v_Luk_23_49] Luke 23:49\nThe women who had fol-\nlowed him in Galilee (cf.\n[v_Luk_8_1] [v_Luk_8_2] [v_Luk_8_3] Luke 8:1-3)\n[v_Jhn_19_25] John `[char_John_Ref]` 19:25\nHis mother\nHis mother\u2019s sister\nMary `[char_Mary_Ref]` the wife of Clopas\nMary Magdalene\nMary Magdalene\nIn recent years the literature on Mary Magdalene\nhas mushroomed. The following list is a sample of\nrecent publications:\nBrock, Ann Graham. Mary Magdalene, the First Apostle:\nThe Struggle for Authority. Cambridge MA: Harvard\nDivinity School,"
